Then, this leg is the one

00:01:45.140 --> 00:01:47.559
to get your balance, leaning over is really easy.

00:01:48.320 --> 00:01:55.899
Swinging back is really easy too. The only problem with mounting your bike from the opposite side is that the kickstand is on THIS side.

00:01:57.920 --> 00:02:01.839
That's pretty easy to flip up, as long as you're looking. Actually...

00:02:03.439 --> 00:02:05.439
I'm trying to do without looking. Ugh! There!

00:02:41.030 --> 00:02:44.960
If you want to ride a bike,  your prosthetic probably has to be cut pretty low and back

00:02:45.450 --> 00:02:52.640
because you bend your knee pretty high at the top of the pedal stroke; and so if your prosthetic is cut too high,

00:02:52.860 --> 00:02:58.490
you won't be able to bend your knee like this, and it'll make riding a bike uncomfortable. So if you have that problem,

00:02:58.490 --> 00:03:04.309
You can go to your prosthetist and ask them to adjust your prosthetic so that you are able to ride a bike.

